  "title": "Marketing Executive | Interior Design Firm | Ubi Office",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Senior Marketing Executive</strong></li><li><strong>Location: Ubi, Singapore</strong></li><li><strong>Salary: $3800 - $4500</strong></li><li><strong>Working Hours: 5 Days | 9am – 6pm</strong></li><li><strong>Singapore Interior Design Firm</strong></li></ul><p><br /><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>1. Degree or diploma in media / design or marketing.<br />2. Prefer to have marketing experience in Interior Firm<br /><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><strong>Branding & Strategy:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Develop and implement a comprehensive brand strategy to establish as a preferred choice in the interior design market.</strong></li><li><strong>Ensure brand messaging and visuals are consistent across all platforms, enhancing customer engagement and loyalty.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Marketing Campaigns:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Design and execute strategic marketing campaigns aimed at increasing website traffic and improving lead conversion rates.</strong></li><li><strong>Collaborate with design and sales teams to align marketing strategies with business objectives, enhancing the sales pipeline.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Digital Marketing:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Expand the company’s digital footprint through effective SEO and SEM strategies to improve search engine rankings and drive organic traffic.</strong></li><li><strong>Manage social media channels to increase engagement and followers, translating into more inquiries and conversions.</strong></li><li><strong>Analyze digital performance metrics to optimize campaigns, ensuring data-driven decisions lead to improved marketing effectiveness.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Content Creation:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Develop and manage content calendars to maintain a consistent flow of engaging content, increasing audience interaction and content sharing.</strong></li><li><strong>Supervise high-quality photo and video production to enhance brand storytelling and showcase projects effectively.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Events & Public Relations:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Organize impactful interior design exhibitions and client events to enhance brand exposure and client satisfaction.</strong></li><li><strong>Leverage media relations and P-R opportunities to increase media mentions and improve public perception of the brand.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Team & Budget Management:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Lead and inspire a marketing team to achieve individual and collective goals, fostering a high-performance culture.</strong></li><li><strong>Efficiently manage the marketing budget to improve marketing ROI, ensuring optimal resource allocation and cost-effectiveness.</strong></li></ul><p><strong></strong></p><p>#SCR-carson-cheong</p><p></p><p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p><p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p><p></p>",
